## Edward M. Kennedy

"Edward Moore Kennedy (February 22, 1932 – August 25, 2009) was an American lawyer and politician from [Massachusetts](/Massachusetts) who served as a member of the [United States Senate](/United_States_Senate) from 1962 until his death in 2009. A member of the [Democratic Party](/Democratic_Party_(United_States)) and the prominent [Kennedy family](/Kennedy_family), he was the [second-most-senior](/List_of_United_States_Senators_in_the_111th_Congress_by_seniority) member of the Senate when he died. He is [ranked fifth in U.S. history for length of continuous service as a senator](/List_of_members_of_the_United_States_Congress_by_longevity_of_service). Kennedy was the younger brother of President [John F. Kennedy](/John_F._Kennedy) and U.S. attorney general and U.S. senator [Robert F. Kennedy](/Robert_F._Kennedy), and the father of U.S. representative [Patrick J. Kennedy](/Patrick_J._Kennedy)."

